### [Proverbs Chapter 1](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 1:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 1:2</span></span>

To know - Written to help men to know throughly and practically. Both
human wisdom to conduct our affairs in this life, and Divine wisdom.
Instruction - The instructions delivered either by God, or men, in order
to the attainment of wisdom. To perceive - Which teach a man true
understanding.

[Proverbs 1:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 1:3</span></span>

To receive - Willing to receive the counsels of others. Such as makes
men wise and prudent, and to teach just judgments or equity.

[Proverbs 1:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 1:4</span></span>

Simple - Such as want wisdom. Young man - Who wants both experience and
self - government.

[Proverbs 1:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 1:5</span></span>

Will hear - Is willing to learn. Attain to - The art of governing
himself or others.

[Proverbs 1:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 1:7</span></span>

The fear - Reverence and obedience to God. Beginning - The foundation
without which all other knowledge is vain. Fools - That is, wicked men,
are so far from attaining true wisdom, that they despise it, and all the
means of getting it.

[Proverbs 1:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 1:8</span></span>

My son - He speaks to his scholars with paternal authority and
affection. Of thy mother - Those pious instructions, which thy mother
instilled into thee in thy tender years.

[Proverbs 1:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 1:17</span></span>

In vain - The fowler who spreads, his net in the sight of the bird
looseth his labour. But these, are more foolish than the silly birds,
and though they are not ignorant of the mischief which these evil
courses will bring upon themselves, yet they will not take warning.

[Proverbs 1:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 1:18</span></span>

Their own blood - The destruction which they design to others, fall upon
themselves.

[Proverbs 1:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 1:19</span></span>

Greedy - That seeks gain by wicked practices.

[Proverbs 1:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 1:20</span></span>

Wisdom - Having expressed the counsels of wicked men, he now declares
the voice of wisdom. By wisdom he understands the wisdom of God revealed
to men in his word. And this is said to cry with a loud voice, to
intimate God's earnestness in inviting sinners to repentance. Abroad -
Or, in the streets or open places. Not in corners, but openly before all
the world.

[Proverbs 1:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 1:21</span></span>

Gates - Where magistrates sit in judgment, and people are assembled. The
city - Not only in the gate, but in every part of the city.

[Proverbs 1:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 1:22</span></span>

Scoffers - That scoff at religion and contemn the word and faithful
ministers of God.

[Proverbs 1:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 1:23</span></span>

My words - By my spirit I will cause you to understand my word.

[Proverbs 1:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 1:24</span></span>

Called - By my ministers, by my judgments, and by the motions of my
spirit and your own conscience.

[Proverbs 1:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 1:26</span></span>

Your fear - The misery you do or should fear.

[Proverbs 1:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 1:28</span></span>

Early - With diligence and fervency.

[Proverbs 1:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 1:29</span></span>

Knowledge - The practical knowledge of God and of their duty.

[Proverbs 1:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">pro 1:31</span></span>

Eat - They should receive punishment answerable to their sins. Filled -
With the fruits of them.

[Proverbs 1:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 1:32</span></span>

Turning - From God. Destroy - Shall prove the occasion of their ruin, by
making them presumptuous, and secure.

